question.text:
Match the organisms given in column I with their respective phylum given in column II and select the correct option from the codes given below.
 
Column I (Organisms) Column II (Phylum)
I. Sea Anemone A. Platyhelminthes
II. Liver fluke B. Echinodermata
III. Ascaris C. Coelenterata
IV. Asterias D. Aschelminthes

solution.text:
Sea Anemone or Adamsia belongs to phylum Coelenterata or Cnidaria.
Liver fluke or Fasciola belongs to phylum Platyhelminthes.
Ascaris belongs to phylum Ascehelminthes.
Asterias or Starfish belongs to phylum Echinodermata.
